b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":44,"category_name":"Events","pr_category_id":"4","title_name":"Facility event Trick or Treasure, available now!","message":"<div>The facility event Trick or Treasure will be starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539756000\\"><\/span>!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>In Trick or Treasure, you can acquire an event-exclusive facility Sweet Retreat.<\/div><div>If you take part in the event, you&#39;ll be able to build this Sweet Retreat in your Halidom!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The Sweet Retreat boosts the stats of light-element adventurers during in the Trick or Treasure event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>It also increases the damage that adventurers deal to enemies during the Trick or Treasure quests.<\/div><div>So if you advance the story, you can level up your Sweet Retreat!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Players can equip event-specific wyrmprints to receive more snack-o&rsquo;-lanterns from events, which are used to upgrade Sweet Retreat.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The wyrmprints have other effects during the event as well, so try to get ahold of them to get hte most out of Trick or Treasure!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Details for the facility event Trick or Treasure are below.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event duration:<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539756000\\"><\/span> \\uff5e <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540533599\\"><\/span><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Rewards available:<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539756000\\"><\/span> \\uff5e <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1541138399\\"><\/span><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Sweet Retreat, the event-exclusive facility:<\/div><div>Building a Sweet Retreat in your Halidom increases the stats of light-element characters.<\/div><div>It also confers a special effect that lets you deal more damage to enemies in these event quests.<\/div><div>The strength of this effect increases as you level up the Sweet Retreat.<\/div><div>This effect only applies for the duration of this event.<\/div><div>You can get snack-o&#39;-lanterns from event quests to level up your Sweet Retreat.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Upgrade item: Snack-o&rsquo;-lanterns:<\/div><div>You can get these from event quests from the Trick or Treasure facility event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Boss battles:<\/div><div>These are quests where players face off against bosses who appear in the event story.<\/div><div>Rewards vary depending on the difficulty selected.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Extra boss battles:<\/div><div>While the difficulty level is higher than normal boss battles, the rewards are generous.<\/div><div>These will unlock at a fixed percentage when you clear the expert version of a boss battle.<\/div><div>The quest will disappear once you clear it.<\/div><div>Once the conditions for the quest are met, you can unlock it repeatedly.<\/div><div>This quest is single player only.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Daily battles:<\/div><div>These are daily quests specific to this event that can only be cleared once a day.<\/div><div>They become unlocked after the first time you clear the boss battle.<\/div><div>These quests offer various kinds of rewards.<\/div><div>You can retry as many times within a day until you are able to clear it.<\/div><div>This quest is single player only.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Challenge battles:<\/div><div>These are high-difficulty fights limited to solo play.<\/div><div>They&#39;re unlocked after beating the boss battle on expert rank.<\/div><div>This quest unfolds across waves of enemies, where even receiving a game over rewards you based on how many waves you cleared.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Tricker Treat rewards:<\/div><div>These are event points exclusive to Trick or Treasure.<\/div><div>They can be earned by clearing event quests.<\/div><div>Collect Tricker Treat rewards and you can acquire prizes.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Treasure Trade rewards:<\/div><div>You can trade Jack Chocolates, which are acquired during quests, and Candy Baskets in at the Treasure Trade for various rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Endeavors:<\/div><div>These endeavors can only be attempted for the duration of the event.<\/div><div>They are separated into Daily and Limited variations.<\/div><div>By accomplishing these endeavors, you can receive various rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Notes:<\/div><div>1. Details for the event endeavors are available by tapping &quot;&quot;Help&quot;&quot; on the event page.<\/div><div>2. You must clear Ch. 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) to participate in event quests.<\/div><div>3. If the event ends while you are in a battle, the battle will continue until the results are determined. You will be able to gain rewards according to the results of the battle.<\/div><div>4. The event schedule and content for Trick or Treasure may change without warning.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost!<\/div>","start_time":1539756000,"prev_article_id":"24","next_article_id":"54","image_path":"","update_time":1541384034}}}'